      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      When the scene is loaded the all parts and associated parts table are created and loaded with data. When the scene is loaded the all parts and associated parts table are created and loaded with data from the all parts list in Inventory and associated parts list that is created in this class.

    • onActionAddPartToProduct

      void onActionAddPartToProduct(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Adds a selected part to the product. Adds a selected part to the associated parts list that belongs to the product.
      Parameters:
      event - the add button under the part table is pressed

    • onActionCancelProductAdd

      void onActionCancelProductAdd(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      Cancels product creation and returns to main form. Cancels product creation, any changes made to the product are lost, and returns to the main form.
      Parameters:
      event - the cancel button is pressed
      Throws:
      IOException

    • onActionRemovePartFromProduct

      void onActionRemovePartFromProduct(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Removes a part from the associated parts list. Asks for confirmation before removing a part from the product's associated parts list and also tells the user if no part has been selected when the button is pressed.
      Parameters:
      event - the remove button is pressed

    • onActionSaveProductAdd

      void onActionSaveProductAdd(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      Adds the new product to the list of all products. Creates a new product using the text fields and the associated products list that is added to the list of all products. Catches exceptions for parsing integer and double variable and checks if min is greater than max and if inv is between min and max.
      Parameters:
      event - the save button is pressed
      Throws:
      IOException

    • onActionAddProductFormSearch

      void onActionAddProductFormSearch(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Searches the parts list for the input in the search field. Searches the parts list and returns either a part with a unique id or parts with names that contain the searched for string. A window pops up to inform the user if no results are found.
      Parameters:
      event - the enter button is pressed when the cursor is in the search box
